{
  "texts": [
    "For nonrelativistic particles for example this reduces to the familiar Larmor formula: P 0 rad ∝ dt ⃗ x 2.",
    "Nonetheless, one could imagine situations where the Coulomb field near infinity is important (see for example the δ(ω) term in [60, eq.",
    "( 8)] in the analysis of angular momentum radiation) and thus we include it in (4.44) for completeness.",
    "9In summary, the general relation between potentials and on-shell fields is given by (4.44) where the first term includes only connected contributions to the KMOC expectation value, which can be computed by the reduction formula (4.45).",
    "The complete formula, however, includes an extra \"Coulomb\" term, which may or may not be relevant depending on the physical situation of interest."
  ]
}